Vice President Biden met with business executives from information technology companies to discuss efforts to help Americans acquire the skills needed for middle-class jobs. He emphasized the importance of teaching skills that are in demand by employers and encouraged the expansion of successful initiatives, such as partnerships between companies and community colleges. The group also discussed the benefits of on-the-job training opportunities, such as apprenticeships, in helping Americans find employment and move into the middle class. The Vice President is working with various organizations and leaders to improve the job-driven and effective workforce and training system.